{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17588302","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17588302"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"answeredAt":null,"options":[],"response":null,"finalizedAt":null},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15128"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17588353","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17588353"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T09:06:24+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T09:06:24+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15128"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15128","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15128"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.12,0.19,0.31,0.31,0.08]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7816"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71654"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7816","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7816"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15128"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57150"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4933"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"7086"},{"type":"tags","id":"7882"},{"type":"tags","id":"8115"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19055"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19059"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23209"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23517"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23911"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71654","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/71654"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ERenal infections are relatively common and a knowledge of renal anatomy and the pathological processes will help decide management.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following statements about renal infections is correct?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Proteus species are the commonest type of renal infection","Perinephric abscesses occur within Gerota\u0027s fascia","Most renal abscesses will require some form of drainage","Haematogenous spread is the most common cause of renal infections","Most renal abscesses are found in patients with kidney stones"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EMost renal infections occur due to ascending infection from the lower urinary tract. \u003Cstrong\u003EHaematogenous\u003C/strong\u003E spread is less common but can occur, particularly in intravenous drug users.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhilst \u003Cstrong\u003EProteus species\u003C/strong\u003E can lead to renal tract infections, the commonest cause is \u003Cem\u003EEscherichia coli.\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EGerota\u0027s fascia is a thin layer of fibrous tissue outside the kidney. Most renal abscesses are confined to the parenchyma, but occasionally may breach the renal capsule and form a\u003Cstrong\u003E perinephric abscess within Gerota\u0027s fascia\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMost renal abscesses are found in patients with diabetes, although \u003Cstrong\u003Ekidney stones\u003C/strong\u003E are an important risk factor, but less so than diabetes. When abscess do occur, they can usually be treated with intravenous antibiotics and those less than 3-5 cm will have a good chance of complete resolution. Larger abscesses will usually require some \u003Cstrong\u003Eform of drainage\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Ascending urinary tract infections are the most common cause of renal infections","Haematogenous spread can cause renal abscesses, particularly in intravenous drug users"],"references":["Sabih A, Leslie SW. Complicated Urinary Tract Infections. 2023 Nov 12. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 28613784","Bilsen MP, Jongeneel RMH, Schneeberger C, Platteel TN, van Nieuwkoop C, Mody L, Caterino JM, Geerlings SE, K\u00f6ves B, Wagenlehner F, Conroy SP, Visser LG, Lambregts MMC. Definitions of Urinary Tract Infection in Current Research: A Systematic Review. Open Forum Infect Dis. 2023 Jun 27;10(7):ofad332. doi: 10.1093/ofid/ofad332. PMID: 37426954; PMCID: PMC10323732","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57150"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15128"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57150","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/57150"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-20T10:24:37+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-20T10:25:08+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7816"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71654"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":